The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 October is 78,327 (9,027.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 September, there were 2,562 new confirmed cases (295.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 September, there were 2,162 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 19% (400 extra cases).
